reviewText: This footage from the mid 1990s is a view to a by-gone era in South Florida history! His camp was re-created for the filming, and remnants still exist inside Everglades National Park. It's a bit hard to find, but if you'd like to see pics of what it looks like today, see @ [...]

Tales of the Everglades gives a very good insight about the little known past and present history of the Southwest Florida Coast and the Ten Thousand Islands. Its a story of Totch Brown and the people of the extreme Southwest Coast of Florida. The history of its past was very interesting and so was the life of Totch Brown an alligator hunter, smuggler, fisherman. I liked this video very much with its history and intriguing stories and tall tales!
